A '''Covenant Shadow''',<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide">''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> or '''Covenant Shadow agent''',<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 27">[[Knights of the Old Republic 27|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 27]]</ref> was a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] agent under the [[Jedi Covenant]] who had every last bit of information about their existence erased from all official documentation. They were known to only a few members of the Jedi Covenant. Separate from the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], the Covenant Shadows were based on the same concept as [[Jedi Shadow]]s, though these agents were tasked with hunting down [[Sith artifact/Legends|Sith artifacts]]. Among some of the captured treasures were the last [[Epistle of Marka Ragnos]], [[Jori Daragon's amulet]] and the [[Eye of Horak-mul]]. Around [[3963 BBY]], agent [[Celeste Morne]] was given the task of finding the [[Muur Talisman]] on [[Taris/Legends|Taris]]. At this time, there were at least thirty Covenant Shadows.

